{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015SjEK5jCJULZ2VXdp4XLbV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KDARSjTcgpejEVRGMNxPLU","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The embedding vector produced for a given query string has the correct dimensionality for the vector database index.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: The failure mode is 'wrong model configured' or 'API response format changed so dimension is misread.' An in-process stub always returns a correctly-shaped vector, making the test trivially pass regardless of what the real embedding service returns. The real failure only surfaces when the system makes an actual HTTP call to the embedding endpoint with the production configuration and the returned shape is verified against the configured DB index. LLM-DEP: Dimensionality is deterministic for a given model—no non-determinism, so Agentic is not required. REJECTION-GATE: Why not Integration? Any in-process fake embedding client returns whatever dimension we program into it; the test then validates our own stub rather than the real service contract.","test_description":"Configure the system with the real embedding service and the real (or real-schema) vector DB index config. Issue a representative query string through the full embedding path, capture the returned vector, and assert its dimension equals the index's configured dimension. Run against the live embedding endpoint to catch configuration drift.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.13,"System":0.58,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The similarity search returns results ordered by descending cosine similarity score.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure is at the boundary between the query layer and the vector DB: either the DB returns results 